Pre-Game Insights: Harambee Stars midfielder Teddy Akumu is hungry to qualify for the Cup of Nations and believes the team can make it to the tournament despite a tough group.
Akumu thinks the momentum the team has picked up in the last few international matches will be good enough to push them into the game against Zimbabwe.
It will be important for Kenya to win their first game against Zimbabwe to give them a good footing into the rest of the matches.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Kenya starts the qualification journey for the Africa Cup of Nations against Zimbabwe on Friday evening in Kampala, Uganda.
The country is also pooled with Namibia, who they play next Tuesday in South Africa, as well as Cameroon.
Others: Teddy Akumu was dropped from the Harambee Stars final squad that travelled to Egypt in 2019.
